# Preserve Comments During Refactoring

When refactoring code, **never delete or omit existing comments**. Comments are documentation — losing them makes the code harder to read.

## Rules

- **Move comments** with the code they describe. If a block moves to a new file/function, its comments go with it.
- **Update comments** if the refactor changes behavior, but never just drop them.
- **Section separators** (e.g. `// ====`, `// ---`) must also be preserved if the surrounding structure still exists.
- If a comment becomes stale after refactoring, **rewrite it** to reflect the new reality — do not delete it.
